Subject: Re: [T2] fixing value tube leaks

On 11/22/06 6:20 PM, "Mike Soultanian" <msoultan(-at-)csulb.edu> wrote:

> I put new valve tube gaskets on, but a couple of them are leaking so my
> mechanic recommended that I use this on the gaskets and they won't leak:
> 
> http://tinyurl.com/yhj8de

Loctite 565 works better. Put a very thin coating on the tube, install the
o-ring, then another very thin coating of the 565. I use a paint brush to
apply it. They never leak. 565 is very flexible so it moves with the engine
parts.


